<div id="outline-container-motivation" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="motivation">motivation</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-motivation">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>in this course we teach you

<ul class="org-ul">
<li>to combine rigorous economics</li>
<li>and how to present it in an understandable way</li>
<li>while your results can be easily reproduced</li>
</ul></li>

<li>in the python track we do this by teaching you

<ul class="org-ul">
<li>a programming language: python</li>
<li>how to create notebooks where you can explain your code and</li>
<li>publish them on-line</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-examples" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="examples">things to learn</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-examples">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>when you finish this course, you can

<ul class="org-ul">
<li>solve models in python</li>
<li>do simulations in python</li>
<li>create a file or notebook like <a href="https://github.com/janboone/applied-economics/blob/master/economics_notebook.ipynb">this</a></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-finishing-the-course" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="finishing-the-course">finishing the course</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-finishing-the-course">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>helps you to present economics in a way that is

<ul class="org-ul">
<li>understandable and</li>
<li>reproducible</li>
</ul></li>

<li>gives a good starting point to write your thesis</li>
<li>check <a href="index.html">the website</a> and Canvas for relevant information</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
